
This is at least a partial list of people who have contributed to Voidface.
It is sorted by name. Please add yourself in alphabetical order when you
submit your first patch.

    Voidface contributors
        Initial repository scaffold; core training loop design;
        adversarial-ensemble architecture.


The following prior works materially shaped Voidface's design. We list them
here in gratitude:

    PhotoGuard                MIT CSAIL — encoder-attack framing.
                              Salman, Ilyas, Madry et al., ICML 2023.

    Fawkes / LowKey / Glaze   UChicago SAND Lab — the shipped desktop
                              cloaking paradigm.

    Anti-DreamBooth           Le et al. — alternating training defense.

    AdvPaint / DiffusionGuard Inpainting-specific defense literature that
                              directly informed the nudify threat model.

    NullSwap                  ICCV 2025 — proof that a well-targeted
                              identity attack can still work against
                              modern face-swap models.

    Silencer                  CVPR 2025 — the anti-purification objective
                              we adopt for restorer-in-the-loop training.

    Radiya-Dixit & Tramer     ICLR 2022 — the paper that killed Fawkes
                              and taught us not to overpromise.

    Honig et al.              UMD 2024 — "Adversarial Perturbations
                              Cannot Reliably Protect Artists." Read it.

    IMPRESS (Cao et al.)      NeurIPS 2023 — showed the DiffPure-style
                              purification attack we must survive.
